-provider is a component that makes the store accessible to every component in the
app

-React Components calls a action creator return an action sent to reducers, updates
states in store, state sent back to components causing them to rerender

-provider tag is a react tag that is provided by the react-redux library

-the sole purpose of react-redux library is to make sure that react and redux works
together nicely

-Nested components can access the global state by reaching directly into redux store
